  "prompt": "Did islam exist before prophet mohmmad?",
  "response": "Islam, as it is known today, was formally established with the teachings and revelations received by the Prophet Muhammad in the 7th century CE. However, Muslims believe that Islam is not a new religion introduced by Muhammad but rather the final and complete revelation of a monotheistic faith that has been present since the time of earlier prophets.\n\n**Understanding Islam in Context:**\n\n1. **Abrahamic Tradition:** Islam is part of the Abrahamic tradition, which includes Judaism and Christianity. Muslims believe that prophets such as Adam, Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus preached the message of monotheism (the belief in one God) and submission to God's will\u2014core tenets of Islam.\n\n2. **Continuity of Message:** According to Islamic belief, the essence of Islam\u2014submission to one God and living a righteous life\u2014has been a consistent message throughout human history. Each prophet brought guidance suited to the context of their time, but the fundamental principles remained the same.\n\n3. **Language and Terminology:** The term \"Islam\" (meaning \"submission\" in Arabic) specifically refers to the message and practice as revealed to Muhammad. While the core monotheistic principles existed before, the formalized religion with its specific scriptures (like the Quran) and practices was established with Muhammad.\n\n4. **Pre-Islamic Practices:** In the Arabian Peninsula before Muhammad, various forms of monotheism and polytheism coexisted. Some tribes adhered to monotheistic beliefs, which Islam later unified and expanded upon.\n\n**Scholarly Perspectives:**\n\n- **Historical View:** From a historical standpoint, Islam as a distinct religious tradition emerged in the 7th century. There were no organized Islamic communities before Muhammad.\n\n- **Theological View:** Theologically, Muslims view Islam as the original faith of all prophets, with each prophet reaffirming the same fundamental message. Thus, while the organized religion of Islam began with Muhammad, its spiritual essence is considered eternal in Islamic belief.\n\n**Conclusion:**\n\nIn summary, while the organized religion of Islam with its specific doctrines, scriptures, and practices began with the Prophet Muhammad, the underlying principles of submission to one God and righteous living are viewed in Islamic theology as timeless and present in previous prophetic messages. Therefore, Islam in its current form did not exist before Prophet Muhammad, but its foundational beliefs are believed to have always been part of the divine guidance to humanity.",
